## Context

`tests/test_script_hygiene.py` pins its enumeration to `scripts/`, so
entry-point `.py` files under `deliverables/**/` (probe scripts such as
`revision-rdj26561/probe_bib_vs_corpus.py` and
`probe_prior_mappings_overlap.py`) escape the argparse/io-discipline sweep.
They currently comply voluntarily; the rule is untested there. Surfaced by
the 0289 `/verify-adherence` pass.

## Relevant files

- `tests/test_script_hygiene.py` — enumeration pinned to `SCRIPTS_DIR`
- `deliverables/data-paper/revision-rdj26561/*.py` — the escaping scripts

## Actions

1. Add an adherence test enumerating `deliverables/**/*.py` entry points
   (`__name__ == "__main__"` present) and asserting `ArgumentParser` use.

## Test

- The new adherence test itself; prove its teeth by feeding it a fixture
  (or temporarily mutated probe) without argparse.

## Verification

- [ ] `make lint` green; mutation of a probe's argparse trips the test

